headline: Has Costco’s Premium Price Still Got Room To Run After Recent Share Pullback?
summary: If you are wondering whether Costco Wholesale at around $922 a share is still a smart buy or if the value story has already played out, you are not alone. That is exactly what we are going to unpack here. The stock has slipped 0.6% over the last month and is down 6.4% over the past year, but those moves sit on top of a powerful longer term run, with 99.4% returns over 3 years and 160.4% over 5 years that still have many investors firmly in the bull camp.
